# deps

Renders the dependency whitelist as a continuation sub-block within the `## [ENVIRONMENT RUNTIME & LANGUAGE]` section opened by the lang template. The prohibition prefix is fixed — it activates strict compliance behavior in the model for package selection.

# entity Input

- directive: 'deps'
- name: undefined — deps is always anonymous
- body: the dependency list and constraints

# entity Output

```markdown
### Approved Dependency Whitelist

You are strictly forbidden from installing or importing any package outside of this list:

{{body}}
```

# rule

- deps blocks carry no name. A name field on a deps block is a PARSE_ERROR.
- This template emits no `##` section header — it renders as a `###` sub-section inside the lang section. The compiler must output this block immediately after lang.
- Multiple deps blocks from different cascade levels are merged in cascade order. The compiler concatenates their bodies with a blank line before binding — the AI sees the complete whitelist in one block.
